children.text: The contract drawings I have been provided show that the elevation plans for several wet area rooms are tiled across the walls, however the wall sheets have not been fixed back to the wall studs at the required centres within the area.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The wall sheet manufacturer’s installation manual requires that plasterboard in tiled areas be installed in accordance with Figure 32, see below;
The builder must establish the weight of the wall tiles to be installed to these wall areas and properly fix these sheets to the wall studs at the required centres.
